"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The code incorrectly uses the `np.insert` function. The `np.insert` function is being called with the first argument as a 1D slice of the 2D array `arr`, which is correct. However, the second argument (the index where the value is to be inserted) is set to 1, which is valid for a 1D array. The issue arises because the `np.insert` function does not modify the original array in place; it returns a new array. Therefore, the assignment `arr[i] = np.insert(arr[i], 1, 3)` will lead to a shape mismatch since `np.insert` will return an array of shape (5,) instead of (4,). This will cause an error when trying to assign it back to `arr[i]` which expects a shape of (4,).\",\n  \"patch\": \"6c6\\n<     arr[i] = np.insert(arr[i], 1, 3)\\n---\\n>     arr[i] = np.insert(arr[i], 1, 3).reshape(1, -1)\"\n}"